"platform_override=win) on Windows. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:38
msgid ""
"For convenience, elements of the target tuple that are omitted will be "
"inferred, so the above could be written:"
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:45
msgid ""
"Toolchain names that don't name a channel instead can be used to name "
"[custom toolchains](#custom-toolchains)."
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:51
msgid "Custom toolchains"
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:53
msgid ""
"For convenience of developers working on Rust itself, `rustup` can manage "
"local builds of the Rust toolchain. To teach `rustup` about your build, run:"
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:60
msgid ""
"For example, on Ubuntu you might clone `rust-lang/rust` into `~/rust`, build "
"it, and then run:"
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:68
msgid ""
"Now you can name `my-toolchain` as any other `rustup` toolchain. Create a "
"`rustup` toolchain for each of your `rust-lang/rust` workspaces and test "
"them easily with `rustup run my-toolchain rustc`."
msgstr ""

#: src/concepts/toolchains.md:72
msgid ""
"Because the `rust-lang/rust` tree does not include Cargo, _when `cargo` is "
"invoked for a custom toolchain and it is not available, `rustup` will "
"attempt to use `cargo` from one of the release channels_, preferring "
"'nightly', then 'beta' or 'stable'."
msgstr ""
